
A:
	Who is that beautiful woman over there? I have never seen something so exquisite.

B:
	That

A:
	[_Speaking very slowly_.]  That our lives may drift
apart.

B:
	You haven't even met her yet.

A:
	I know I just met you, but I love you with all my heart.

B:
	I thought we were talking about the woman over there? [points]

A:
	I have been thinking about nothing else.

B:
	I can't believe you waited so long to tell me.

A:
	You killed my cousin? And now I can never see you again? I cannot live any more.

B:
	But you just said you loved me with all your heart?

A:
	Forget!

B:
	I could never forget that! Because I love you too!

A:
	With you dead, what keeps me alive?

B:
	I am still here! Look at me!

A:
	Yes, yes. The time has come now.

B:
	What is happening?
